main event: A civilian reported observing shapes or lights arranged in patterns over Colmar Manor, MD on either March 28 or 29, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as traveling at high speed and high altitude., The witness kept the objects in sight for over 1 minute., One witness described the formation as resembling a 'V' shape., The objects were noted to have a grey color and glaring position., The report indicated that the sightings were uninvestigated due to insufficient data.
sighted object: forms or lights arranged in shapes
